<paragraph blockId="13.[160,1155,1494,1727]" lastBlockId="14.[160,1156,142,270]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="617" pageId="13" pageNumber="616">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1882" box="[284,365,1530,1554]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Hircella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="616" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[284,365,1530,1554]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="616">Hircella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was established specifically for 
<taxonomicName authority="(Haswell, 1879 b)" baseAuthorityName="Haswell" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[722,1045,1530,1554]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Hircella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="616" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornigera">
<emphasis box="[722,853,1530,1554]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="616">H. cornigera</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Haswell WA" box="[867,1037,1530,1554]" pageId="13" pageNumber="616" pagination="319 - 351" refId="ref17914" refString="Haswell WA. 1879 b. On some additional new genera and species of amphipodus crustaceans. Proc Linn Soc N S W. 4: 319 - 351 + pls 18 - 24." type="journal article" year="1879">Haswell, 1879b</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mayer P" pageId="13" pageNumber="616" pagination="1 - 160" refId="ref18507" refString="Mayer P. 1903. Die Caprellidae der Siboga-Expedition. Siboga-Expeditie, Monographie. 34: 1 - 160 + pls 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1903">Mayer (1903)</bibRefCitation>
. Recently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Guerra-Garcia JM &amp; Takeuchi I" box="[361,764,1565,1589]" pageId="13" pageNumber="616" pagination="967 - 1044" refId="ref17797" refString="Guerra-Garcia JM, Takeuchi I. 2004. The Caprellidea (Crustacea: Amphipoda) from Tasmania, Australia. J Nat Hist. 38: 967 - 1044." type="journal article" year="2004">Guerra-García and Takeuchi (2004)</bibRefCitation>
described the second species of 
<emphasis box="[160,246,1599,1623]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="616">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1882" box="[160,242,1599,1623]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Hircella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="616" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hircella</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Guerra-Garcia and Takeuchi, 2004" authorityName="Guerra-Garcia and Takeuchi" authorityYear="2004" box="[256,762,1599,1623]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Hircella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="616" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis box="[256,367,1599,1623]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="616">H. inermis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Guerra-Garcia JM &amp; Takeuchi I" box="[377,762,1599,1623]" pageId="13" pageNumber="616" pagination="967 - 1044" refId="ref17797" refString="Guerra-Garcia JM, Takeuchi I. 2004. The Caprellidea (Crustacea: Amphipoda) from Tasmania, Australia. J Nat Hist. 38: 967 - 1044." type="journal article" year="2004">Guerra-García and Takeuchi, 2004</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the Tasmanian coast. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mayer P" pageId="13" pageNumber="616" pagination="1 - 160" refId="ref18507" refString="Mayer P. 1903. Die Caprellidae der Siboga-Expedition. Siboga-Expeditie, Monographie. 34: 1 - 160 + pls 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1903">Mayer (1903)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that pereopod 5 of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1882" box="[625,706,1634,1658]" class="Malacostraca" family="Caprellidae" genus="Hircella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="616" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[625,706,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="616">Hircella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was completely degenerate, and the diagnosis of 
<bibRefCitation author="Takeuchi I" box="[302,479,1669,1693]" pageId="13" pageNumber="616" pagination="947 - 964" refId="ref19030" refString="Takeuchi I. 1993. Is the Caprellidea a monophyletic group? J Nat Hist. 27: 947 - 964." type="journal article" year="1993">Takeuchi (1993)</bibRefCitation>
followed his conclusion. Since the 
<typeStatus box="[872,922,1669,1693]" pageId="13" pageNumber="616">type</typeStatus>
specimen deposited in the Australian Museum is lost (
<bibRefCitation author="Springthorpe R &amp; Lowry JK" box="[548,893,1703,1727]" pageId="13" pageNumber="616" pagination="1 - 134" refId="ref18770" refString="Springthorpe R, Lowry JK. 1994. Catalogue of crustacean type specimens in the Australian Museum: Malacostraca. Tech Rep Aust Mus. 11: 1 - 134." type="journal article" year="1994">Springthorpe and Lowry 1994</bibRefCitation>
), this new diagnosis is based on recently collected specimens from the Solitary Islands, 
<collectingRegion box="[941,1152,142,166]" country="Australia" name="New South Wales" pageId="14" pageNumber="617">New South Wales</collectingRegion>
. Observation revealed that pereopod 5 is composed of one tiny article and the number of articles in the flagellum of antenna 2 increases from two to three during growth (see 
<figureCitation box="[160,267,246,270]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1515,1538]" captionTargetBox="[163,1151,142,1483]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[163,1153,142,1484]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 10. Hircella cornigera (Haswell, 1879b) from Solitary Islands, Coffs Harbour, and out of Jervis Bay, New South Wales. Number of articles in the flagellum of antenna 2 against the body length." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3985757" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3985757/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="617">Figure 10</figureCitation>
). Hence, the generic diagnosis of the present genus is revised as above.
</paragraph>
